ResponseRules.description: Voice sample messages the player finds in Crew Quarters and uses to reconstruct Fiona's voice so he can get into Deep Storage.

ResponseRule.name: Danielle: Message to Will Mitchell
ResponseRule.description: Establishes a rapport and a clearly different way of speaking for Mitchell to conflict with the Luka encounter to come, and it also explains why Skillet has the odd dialect that he does. Mitchell is a bit sensitive, mostly cheerful, and his voice is slightly high. He takes his role as the kitchen cook with a little flair, and that's what possessed him to make the modification to Skillet. It's possible to cut the first 2 sentences. In addition, the use of Skillet here is intended as a clear audio signpost that when the player comes to the kitchen, the man there is clearly not Mitchell.

ResponseRule.name: Danielle_ComputerMessage
ResponseRule.description: A file stored on Fiona's computer. A "yes" from Sam when she timidly asks her out on a date. This is a voice sample the player can find to trick the voice lock and it also shows Fiona's more shy vulbnerable personal side. She doesn't do people that well. Contrasting Sam's more straightforward, brash attitude with Fiona's more reserved one.
